==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thursday
<hw>Thurs"day</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧ursdei</ets>, <ets>⟦thorn⟧orsday</ets>, from the Scand. name
<ets>Thor</ets> + E. <ets>day</ets>. Icel. <ets>⟦thorn⟧⟦omac⟧rr</ets>
Thor, the god of thunder, is akin to AS. <ets>⟦thorn⟧unor</ets> thunder;
D. <ets>Donderdag</ets> Thursday, G. <ets>Donnerstag</ets>, Icel.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧⟦omac⟧rsdagr</ets>, Sw. & Dan. <ets>Torsdag</ets>. ⟦root⟧52.
See <er>Thor</er>, <er>Thunder</er>, and <er>Day</er>.]</ety> <def>The
fifth day of the week, following Wednesday and preceding
Friday.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Holy Thursday</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Holy</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thurst</ent>⟦br⟧
